{
  "texts": [
    "It is used to predict unknown regression coefficients in a standard linear regression model.",
    "Instead of explicitly regressing the dependent variable on the independent variable, PCR uses the principal components of the explanatory factors as regressors.",
    "Because only a subset of all the principle components is often employed for regression, PCR is both a regularized process and a shrinkage estimator.",
    "One of the most common applications of PCR is to solve the multicollinearity problem, which occurs when two or more input variables are nearly collinear.",
    "By removing part of the lowvariance principal components in the regression step, PCR can effectively cope with such situations."
  ]
}